cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.MM, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with wireless networks and communication, which falls under the category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The use of compressed sensing for decoding messages suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory). The iterative algorithm based on belief propagation suggests that the paper could belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The use of randomly distributed on-slots and off-slots suggests that the paper could belong to cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the numerical results and comparison with slotted ALOHA and CSMA suggest that the paper could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
